Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code within the curly braces will be executed. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  printf("You are eligible to vote.");
} else {
  printf("You are not eligible to vote.");
}
```

In this example, the if statement checks if the age variable is greater than or equal to 18. If it is, the code within the curly braces will be executed, and a message will be printed stating that the person is eligible to vote. If the condition is false, the else statement will be executed, and a message will be printed stating that the person is not eligible to vote.
